The article is a statement made by the President of the United States on January 28, 2009, regarding the House passage of the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act. The President emphasizes the urgent need for action in response to the loss of jobs and the plans of major employers to cut even more jobs. He expresses gratitude to the House of Representatives for moving the plan forward, highlighting its various benefits such as doubling renewable energy capacity, lowering healthcare costs, modernizing classrooms, and providing tax relief for working families. The President also emphasizes the importance of creating new jobs and promises transparency and accountability in the administration of the recovery plan. He urges swift action in the Senate and calls for bipartisan cooperation to put Americans back to work.